sentences: Françoise de Clossey (born October 12, 1974) is a Canadian pianist and organist.

Recently, she signed an important contract for a series of recordings in duet with Mauro Maur, with whom she has collaborated since 2003 with great public and critical success all over the world, which emphasizes the uniqueness of this duet and the freshness and musicality of its interpretations.
Françoise de Clossey received the Prize Oder 2008 for her career.
Françoise de Clossey was honoured with the International "Beato Angelico" Prize for the Woman of the year 2006.
